Title : Portal:Current events/2014 April 30
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|04|30}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[Al-Qaeda insurgency in Yemen]]:
**At least 30 people have been killed in clashes between [[Al-Qaeda]] and the [[Yemen Army]]. [http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Middle-East/2014/Apr-29/254829-30-dead-as-yemen-army-launches-new-assault-on-qaeda.ashx#axzz30LUUnOrr (''Daily Star'')]
*[[Syrian Civil War]]
**The [[Local Coordination Committees of Syria]] announces that 25 children were killed on Wednesday when [[Syrian Army|Syrian army forces]] dropped [[Barrel bomb|barrel bombs]] on an elementary school.  [http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/30/world/meast/syria-civil-war/index.html?hpt=wo_c2 (BBC)]
*An [[April 2014 Ürümqi attack|explosion in]] the [[Ürümqi Railway Station]] results in three people killed, with another 79 people injured. [http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702303948104579533541934838878 ''(The Wall Street Journal)'']

;Business and economy
*[[India]] has become the world's third-largest economy in [[purchasing power parity]] after the [[United States]] and [[China]], moving ahead of [[Japan]] according to [[World Bank]] report. The last survey in 2005 had placed India in 10th place.[http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/indicators/india-displaces-japan-to-become-third-largest-world-economy-in-terms-of-ppp-world-bank/articleshow/34392694.cms (Times of India)] 
*A [[ground stop]] is issued by the [[Federal Aviation Administration]] for multiple airports in [[Southern California]] due to a computer issue. [http://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/local/LAX-ground-stop-flights-257410331.html (NBC Los Angeles)]

;Disasters
*A gas explosion in a prison in the US town of [[Pensacola, Florida]] reportedly kills at least two people, injures 100 and forces an evacuation. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-27234582 (BBC)]

;Law and crime
*[[Sinn Féin]] leader [[Gerry Adams]] is arrested by police for the [[murder of Jean McConville]], a 37-year-old widowed mother of ten, who was abducted from her home in 1972. [https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-27232731 (BBC)]
*The [[Hassanal Bolkiah|Sultan of Brunei]] has announced a controversial new penal code that will eventually include stoning, amputation and flogging as punishments, as 'Phase one' of [[Sharia|Islamic law]]. [http://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia-pacific/2014/04/brunei-adopts-phase-one-islamic-law-201443051454609650.html (Al Jazeera)]
*A shooting occurs at a [[sawmill]] in [[Nanaimo|Nanaimo, British Columbia]], [[Canada]], killing two people and injuring two others. A former employee is arrested. [http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/kevin-douglas-addison-charged-in-nanaimo-b-c-sawmill-shooting-1.2628033 (CBC.ca)]

;Politics and elections
*[[Iraqi parliamentary election, 2014|Iraqi parliamentary election]]:
**Voters in [[Iraq]] go to the polls for parliamentary elections that have already been marred by violence from the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]]. [http://www.sbs.com.au/news/storystream/iraq-general-election-pm-says-victory-certain (SBS Australia)]
*[[Indian general election, 2014|Indian general election]]
**Voting is in progress in 89 [[List of constituencies of the Lok Sabha|constituencies]] spread across seven [[States and union territories of India|states]] and two [[States and union territories of India|union territories]].[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-27216730 (BBC)]
**138 million people are to vote today in India. The fate of big politicians like, [[Sonia Gandhi]], [[Narendra Modi]], [[LK Advani]] and [[Arun Jaitley]] will be decided in today's polling.[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Lok-Sabha-elections/liveblog/34403471.cms (Times Of India)] 
*Protesters in the [[Nigeria]]n capital [[Abuja]] hold a "million woman" march over the mass kidnapping of schoolgirls by the [[Boko Haram]] terrorist group two weeks ago. [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/30/million-woman-march-over-nigerian-kidnappings (''The Guardian'')]
*[[List of mayors of Toronto|Mayor]] of [[Toronto]] [[Rob Ford]] takes a leave of absence to help with [[substance abuse]], according to his lawyer. [http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/rob-ford-taking-leave-of-absence-lawyer-says-1.2627832 (CBC)]

